title: La derrota
new-page: true

= La derrota

There is no communiqué, because there is no one left to sign one.

It did not happen on a single day. It happened the way the state prefers: a raid here, a defection there, a treasurer with a new job in a ministry, a printing press sold for parts, three cadres in the ground and thirty in exile and the rest simply gone home, which is where most defeats live. The files in Bucareli are complete now, and closed, which is the only form of peace the Republic ever offered you.

Somewhere a teacher keeps a membership card at the bottom of a drawer. Somewhere a railwayman still knows the pension tables by heart. The state has learned nothing, and will be astonished — genuinely astonished — when, years from now, it all begins again under other names. It always begins again. But not with you.

- @fin: Fin.

